0at%20Doordash%20for%20another%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20saw%20colleagues%20and%20friends%20get%20overlooked%20for%20promotions.%20There%20are%20several%20reasons%20for%20this%20%E2%80%94%20here%20are%20four%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22acece069-449e-463e-b021-5d6379493ddd%5C%22%3E1.%20Performance%20gap%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20one%20is%20a%20gap%20in%20performance.%20There%20could%20be%20a%20misalignment%20in%20how%20an%20employee%20thinks%20they're%20doing%20and%20how%20management%20thinks%20they're%20doing%2C%20most%20likely%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20are%20bad%20at%20giving%20feedback.%20An%20employee%20could%20have%20poor%20communication%20skills%2C%20a%20negative%20attitude%2C%20or%20be%20a%20pessimist%2C%20but%20they%20may%20not%20know%20it.%20Or%2C%20when%20they%20do%20receive%20feedback%2C%20they%20argue%20about%20it%20instead%20of%20trying%20to%20remediate%20and%20improve.%20These%20things%20surface%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20for%20a%20promotion%2C%20but%20they're%20hard%20to%20fix%20when%20you're%20unaware%20it's%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20looking%20for%20a%20promotion%2C%20make%20sure%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-from-a-recruiter-how-to-ask-for-feedback-after-a-job-rejection-2013-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eask%20for%20feedback%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20your%20current%20performance%20and%20actually%20listen.%20Then%2C%20document%20the%20feedback%2C%20improve%2C%20and%20ask%20your%20manager%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20help%20me%20understand%20the%20gap%20between%20where%20I'm%20at%20and%20the%20next%20level%3F%26quot%3B%20That%20way%2C%20you%20may%20get%20promoted%20in%20the%20next%20round%20of%20promotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20your%20one-on-one%20meetings%20after%20the%20initial%20conversation%2C%20you%20could%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20we%20talked%20about%20in%20the%20past%2C%20and%20this%20is%