don't%20always%20have%20fuzzy%20feelings%20about%20product%20managers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-helping-people-leave-twitter-bluesky-tweets-perserve-social-media-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Fa%3E%20abounds%20with%20snarky%20memes%20about%20their%20purposelessness%2C%20their%20illiteracy%20of%20Python%20and%20C%2B%2B%2C%20their%20penchant%20for%20saying%20%26quot%3Bno%20updates%20from%20me%26quot%3B%20in%20update%20meetings.%20On%20forums%20and%20subreddits%2C%20their%20more-technical%20colleagues%20belittle%20their%20work%20as%20fluff.%20%26quot%3BIs%20product%20manager%20the%20most%20useless%20role%20in%20tech%3F%26quot%3B%20an%20engineer%20posted%20on%20Blind.%20Another%20accused%20product%20managers%20of%20%26quot%3Bstealing%20a%20living%26quot%3B%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20an%20engineer%2C%20I%20feel%20I%20can%20easily%20do%20their%20job%20in%20addition%20to%20mine%20with%20not%20much%20extra%20effort%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20One%20person%20on%20Reddit%20argued%20that%20product%20managers%20%26quot%3Bjust%20attend%20meetings%20and%20get%20paid%20more%20than%20the%20actual%20people%20doing%20the%20work.%26quot%3BIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-broken-linkedin-ai-fix-fewer-jobs-resume-spammers-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20post%20titled%20%26quot%3BProduct%20is%20too%20important.%20So%20we%20got%20rid%20of%20product%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20founder%20of%20a%20digital%20banking%20startup%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BAny%20function%20that%20needs%20a%20decade%20to%20explain%20what%20it%20actually%20is%20or%20isn't%20doing%20is%20at%20very%20high%20risk%20of%20somehow%20being%20lost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20companies%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-new-side-hustle-getting-rich-airbnb-super-hosts-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbnb%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Snap%2C%20are%20now%20reconsidering%20the%20utility%20of%20product%20managers%20entirely%2C%20while%20others%20claim%20that%20the%20product%20manager's%20reign%20will%20only%20expand%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI.%20How%20did%20a%20role%20that%20barely%20existed%20before%20the%202000s%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20and%20controversial%20presences%C2%A0in%20tech%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20seed%20of%20product%20management%20dates%20back%20to%20at%20least%20the%201930s%2C%20when%20Procter%20%26amp%3B%20Gamble%20created%20a%20position%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bbrand%20man%26quot%3B%20whose%20job%20it%20was%20to%20understand%20customer%20problems.%20Inspired%20by%20this%2C%20Hewlett-Packard%20pioneered%20the%20tech%20product%20manager%20role%20in%20the%201960s.%20Microsoft%20began%20hiring%20what%20it%20called%20%26quot%3Bprogram%20managers%26quot%3B%20in%20the%201980s.%20In%20the%202000s%2C%20as%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-chip-design-silicon-secret-weapon-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Amazon%20expanded%20to%20create%20ever%20more%20products%2C%20product%20managers%20proliferated.%20Hardware%20and%20software%20also%20became%20more%20complicated%2C%20and%20the%20engineers%20and%20developers%20building%20it%20had%20less%20time%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20was%20actually%20useful%20%E2%80%94%20companies%20realized%20they%20needed%20someone%20dedicated%20to%20translating%20customer%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProduct%20became%20a%20path%20into%20tech%20for%20people%20with%20backgrounds%20in%20consulting%20or%20MBAs.%20A%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20era%26quot%3B%20of%20product%20management%20emerged%20in%20the%20run%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzirp-end-of-cushy-big-tech-job-perks-mass-layoffs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezero%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%202010s.%20Companies%20gobbled%20up%20talent%2C%20sometimes%20hiring%20beyond%20their%20needs%20just%20to%20keep%20smart%20workers%20from%20going%20to%20competitors.%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20became%20bloated%2C%20paying%20middle%20managers%20high%20salaries%20to%20optimize%20products%20and%20development.%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20University%20began%20offering%20what%20it%20calls%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20master's%20degree%20in%20product%20management%20in%202018.%20The%20next%20year%2C%20U.S.%20News%20and%20World%20Report%20named%20product%20manager%20a%20top-five%20job%20for%20MBA%20grads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20shift%20in%20power%20moved%20from%20engineering%20to%20product%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hubert%20Palan%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Productboard%2C%20a%20company%20that%20provides%20software%20for%20product%20managers.%20That's%20part%20of%20the%20friction%3A%20Those%20on%20the%20tech%20side%20often%20think%20the%20product%20manager%20doesn't%20understand%20how%20things%20work%2C%20but%20the%20product%20manager%20may%20think%20the%20engineers%20are%20building%20tools%20that%20people%20don't%20actually%20want%20or%20need%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20feats%20in%20coding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20product%20manager%20is%20at%20the%20center%20of%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Avi%20Siegel%2C%20a%20former%20product%20manager%20who's%20working%20on%20his%20own%20startup%2C%20Momentum.%20%26quot%3BIf%20sales%20wants%20one%20thing%20and%20marketing%20wants%20one%20thing%20and%20customer%20success%20wants%20one%20thing%2C%20they%20disagree%2C%20and%20you%20can%20only%20choose%20one%20of%20the%20groups%20to%20side%20with%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20only%20going%20to%20keep%20one%20of%20those%20people%20happy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProduct%20management%20is%20mostly%20necessary%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20done%20very%20badly%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Aaron%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%20who%20asked%20me%20to%20use%20only%20his%20first%20name.%20He%20says%20he's%20worked%20with%20both%20excellent%20and%20terrible%20product%20managers.%20At%20best%2C%20they%20bear%20the%20burden%20of%20understanding%20the%20tech%20a%20market%20needs.%20At%20worst%2C%20they%20don't%20acknowledge%20how%20technically%20difficult%20a%20solution%20they%20demand%20might%20be%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20ire%2C%20fatigue%2C%20and%20failure.%20%26quot%3BWe%20would%20be%20asked%20for%20the%20moon%20with%20no%20collaboration%2C%26quot%3B%20Aaron%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20their%20coworkers%20are%20happy%20about%20it%20or%20not%2C%20product%20managers%20are%20gaining%20recognition.%20A%202007%20study%20found%20that%20as%20the%20product-management%20role%20became%20more%20formalized%20at%20companies%2C%20projects%20were%20finished%20closer%20to%20deadlines%20and%20with%20more%20predictability.%20A%202020%20report%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-has-a-gen-z-problem-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcKinsey%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bcreating%20a%20comprehensive%20product-management%20function%26quot%3B%20was%20one%20of%20the%20four%20most%20important%20things%20a%20company%20could%20do%20to%20grow%20its%20software%20business%20faster.%20According%20to%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20the%20average%20product%20manager%20in%20the%20US%20makes%20about%20%24160%2C000.%20Software%20engineers%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20average%20about%20%24147%2C000%2C%20and%20tech%20marketing%20specialists%20average%20about%20%2487%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProduct%20managers%20described%20the%20role%20to%20me%20as%20more%20intuitive%20and%20right-brained%20than%20left-brained%20(though%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20technical%20PMs%2C%20many%20of%20them%20former%20engineers).%20The%20career%20site%20Zippia%20says%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20working%20in%20product%20management%20rose%20to%20nearly%2035%25%20in%202021%20from%20about%2019%25%20in%202010.%20That's%20compared%20to%20just%2022%25%20of%20all%20tech%20workers.%20Some%20women%20in%20product%20management%20I%20spoke%20to%20say%20part%20of%20the%20suspicion%20of%20their%20role's%20utility%20could%20be%20rooted%20in%20sexism.%20In%202022%2C%20two%20women%20who%20worked%20as%20product%20managers%20posted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fcoldhealing%2Fstatus%2F1533093790503821315%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%257Ctwcamp%255Etweetembed%257Ctwterm%255E1533093790503821315%257Ctwgr%255E982aa123bfcc7231bfa318bd70e35f3fa9ec56fc%257Ctwcon%255Es1_%26ref_url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.fastcompany.com%252F90760437%252Ftiktok-pool-product-manager%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETikTok%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20explaining%20what%20they%20did%20for%20work%2C%20while%20they%20worked%20from%20a%20pool.%20The%20video%20drew%20hundreds%20of%20harsh%20comments.%20%26quot%3BDealing%20with%20most%20product%20managers%20is%20a%20headache%20and%20a%20half%20and%20we%20usually%20hate%20talking%20to%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20woman%20that%20I've%20met%20with%2C%20if%20they're%20interested%20in%20a%20company%2C%20their%20first%20question%20is%3A%20Am%20I%20technical%20enough%3F%26quot%3B%20Elle%20says.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20guy%20I've%20met%2C%20that%20question%20doesn't%20cross%20their%20mind.%26quot%3B%20It%20makes%20her%20wonder%20if%20it's%20easier%20for%20men%20in%20product%20management%20to%20push%20back%20and%20say%20no%20to%20some%20ideas%20without%20looking%20like%20naysayers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmpathy%20came%20up%20in%20every%20conversation%20I%20had%20for%20this%20story.%20Like%20a%20deft%20diplomat%2C%20a%20good%20product%20manager%20can%20empathize%20with%20the%20needs%20and%20concerns%20of%20every%20stakeholder%2C%20Palan%20says.%20Meg%20Watson%2C%20a%20product%20manager%20who%20has%20worked%20for%20Spotify%20and%20Stitch%20Fix%2C%20says%20product%20managers%20who%20try%20to%20rule%20with%20an%20iron%20fist%20%26quot%3Bquickly%20learn%20that%20doesn't%20work.%26quot%3B%20She%20describes%20working%20as%20a%20product%20manager%20as%20emotional%20and%20intense%20and%20says%20many%20of%20them%20experience%20the%20tension%20of%20their%20role%20daily.%20When%20she%20asks%20people%20looking%20for%20advice%20on%20getting%20into%20product%20management%20why%20they%20want%20to%2C%20they%20say%20they%20want%20power.%20%26quot%3BYou%20will%20have%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20Watson%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20will%20also%20have%20accountability%20and%20pressure%20and%20stress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20some%20companies%20are%20ditching%20them.%20The%20Airbnb%20cofounder%20Brian%20Chesky%20said%20last%20year%20that%20the%20company%20had%20combined%20the%20product-management%20function%20with%20product%20marketing.%20The%20rising%20call%20for%20executives%20to%20go%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-everyone-in-tech-talking-founder-mode-paul-graham-chesky-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efounder%20mode%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20concept%20touted%20by%20Chesky%20and%20coined%20by%20the%20Y%20Combinator%20founding%20partner%20Paul%20Graham%20%E2%80%94%20has%20some%20questioning%20whether%20they%20should%20be%20delegating%20product%20decisions%20to%20product%20managers.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Snap%20told%20The%20Information%20last%20fall%20that%20it%20laid%20off%2020%20product%20managers%20to%20help%20speed%20up%20the%20company's%20decision-making.%20Smaller%20firms%20ponder%20the%20utility%20of%20bringing%20on%20product%20managers%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20others%20say%20the%20scope%20of%20product%20managers%2C%20though%20it%20may%20draw%20engineers'%20ire%2C%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20expand%20across%20the%20industry.%20%26quot%3BThe%20future%20really%20does%20belong%20to%20product%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Frank%20Fusco%2C%20a%20product%20manager%20turned%20CEO%20of%20a%20software%20company%20called%20Silicon%20Society.%20As%20artificial%20intelligence%20