%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Ftipp8h5g_constitution_625x300_20_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20I%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20work%20on%20a%20prestigious%20organisational%20project%20commemorating%20the%2075th%20year%20of%20the%20adoption%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%20A%20large%20part%20of%20it%20involved%20combing%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20debates%20for%20landmark%20speeches%2C%20didactic%20precedents%2C%20and%20various%20values%20of%20constitutionality.%20What%20startled%20me%20were%20the%20many%20humorous%20moments%20in%20the%20debates%2C%20which%20signal%20not%20only%20the%20humanising%20elements%20of%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%94and%20of%20the%20Assembly%20that%20authored%20it%E2%80%94but%20also%20the%20fact%20that%20our%20founding%20parents%20were%20deeply%20in%20touch%20with%20their%20own%20and%20society's%20foibles%2C%20and%20that%20they%20did%20not%20necessarily%20frown%20on%20themselves%20or%20their%20compatriots%20for%20these%20humane%20shortcomings.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20debates%2C%20held%20between%20December%209%2C%201946%2C%20and%20January%2025%2C%201950%2C%20run%20into%20nearly%206%2C000%20pages%20and%203.6%20million%20words.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Nightingale%20Of%20India'%20In%20A%20Male-Dominated%20House%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2011%2C%201946%2C%20when%20Sachchidananda%20Sinha%2C%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Assembly%2C%20invited%20%26quot%3Bbulbul-i-Hind%2C%20the%20Nightingale%20of%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarojini%20Naidu%2C%20to%20address%20the%20House%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20in%20prose%20but%20in%20poetry%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20invitation%20was%20met%20with%20rapture.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20Naidu%20exclaimed%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Chairman%2C%20the%20manner%20of%20your%20calling%20me%20is%20not%20constitutional!%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9COrder%2C%20order%2C%E2%80%9D%20called%20Sinha%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cno%20reflection%20on%20the%20Chair%20please.%E2%80%9D%20Laughter%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20Naidu%20said%20something%20that%20made%20even%20the%20most%20serious%20members%20of%20the%20Assembly%20chuckle.%20%E2%80%9CI%20will%20be%20modest%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9Cemulating%20the%20example%20of%20Rajendra%20Babu%20himself%20and%20confine%20myself%2C%20as%20a%20woman%20should%2C%20to%20purely%20domestic%20issues.%E2%80%9D%20Her%20self-deprecating%20humour%20seemed%20to%20mildly%20rebuke%20an%20ostensibly%20male-dominated%20assembly%E2%80%94there%20were%20only%20fifteen%20women%20back%20then%20in%20an%20assembly%20of%20nearly%20390%20members.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Ambedkar%20Joked%20About%20'Professor'%20Kamath%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2027%2C%201948%2C%20during%20a%20debate%20on%20pensions%20for%20parliamentary%20members%20and%20Prime%20Ministers%20and%20Presidents%2C%20BR%20Ambedkar%20addressed%20HV%20Kamath%20as%20%E2%80%9CProfessor%20Kamath%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20inviting%20him%20to%20share%20his%20thoughts%20on%20residential%20provisions.%20Kamath%2C%20who%20had%20the%20reputation%20of%20being%20a%20fiery%20and%20garrulous%20speaker%2C%20protested%3A%20%E2%80%9CSir%2C%20I%20am%20not%20Professor%20Kamath.%E2%80%9D%20Ambedkar's%20rejoinder%20comprised%20dry%20Anglo-American%20wit.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20he%20is%20quite%20entitled%20to%20be%20called%20Professor%20because%20he%20speaks%20so%20often%2C%E2%80%9D%20remarked%20Ambedkar.%20The%20Assembly%20cracked%20up%2C%20more%20so%20because%20Ambedkar%20was%20not%20known%20to%20display%20his%20witty%20sense%20of%20humour%20very%20often%20in%20the%20Assembly.%20Ambedkar's%20comment%20was%20also%20funny%20because%20he%2C%20himself%2C%20as%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Drafting%20Committee%20for%20the%20Constitution%2C%20is%20known%20to%20have%20spoken%20the%20most%20in%20the%20Assembly%3A%20nearly%202%2C70%2C000%20words.%20The%20reply%20to%20Kamath%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20was%20a%20jovial%20acknowledgement%20of%20his%20credo%2C%20not%20an%20opposition%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20otherwise%20serious%20demeanour%2C%20Ambedkar%20occasionally%20resorted%20to%20humour%20to%20express%20a%20sceptical%20stance%20on%20grave%20matters%2C%20such%20as%20the%20criticism%20against%20the%20Draft%20Constitution.%20In%20one%20instance%2C%20addressing%20critics%20who%20wanted%20a%20Constitution%20based%20on%20ancient%20village-based%20polities%2C%20Ambedkar%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20do%20not%20want%20any%20Central%20or%20Provincial%20Governments.%20They%20just%20want%20India%20to%20contain%20so%20many%20village%20Governments.%20The%20love%20of%20the%20intellectual%20Indians%20for%20the%20village%20community%20is%20of%20course%20infinite%20if%20not%20pathetic.%E2%80%9D%20Hearing%20these%20words%2C%20even%20Ambedkar's%20opponents%20in%20the%20Assembly%20broke%20into%20laughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENotwithstanding%20The%20Word%20'Notwithstanding'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20was%20the%20speech%20of%20PS%20Deshmukh%2C%20who%20later%20became%20India's%20first%20Minister%20for%20Agriculture.%20On%20September%208%2C%201949%2C%20Deshmukh%20remarked%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20the%20comment%20is%20absolutely%20justified%20that%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lawyers'%20constitution%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98Paradise%20for%20lawyers'%2C%20where%2C%20there%20will%20be%20so%20many%20innumerable%20loopholes%20that%20we%20will%20be%20wasting%20years%20and%20years%20before%20we%20could%20come%20to%20the%20final%20and%20correct%20interpretation%20of%20many%20clauses.%E2%80%9D%20Explaining%20his%20point%20further%2C%20he%20took%20up%20the%20example%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98notwithstanding%2C'%20which%20recurs%20in%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20count%20the%20use%20of%20the%20word%20'notwithstanding'%20in%20this%20Constitution%2C%20I%20am%20certain%20that%20the%20number%20of%20times%20that%20word%20is%20used%20will%20far%20exceed%20the%20use%20of%20the%20word%20'Parliament'%20or%20'Constitution'%20in%20the%20whole%20Constitution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2017%20Kamath%20proposed%20to%20move%20a%20singular%20amendment%20meant%20to%20prefix%20the%20phrase%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20name%20of%20God%E2%80%9D%20before%20%E2%80%9CWe%2C%20the%20People%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Preamble%20to%20the%20Constitution.%20Several%20members%20of%20the%20Assembly%2C%20including%20Purnima%20Banerji%2C%20a%20member%20from%20the%20United%20Provinces%2C%20alerted%20the%20Assembly%20to%20the%20ramifications.%20Banerji%20cautioned%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20matter%20of%20God%E2%80%9D%20could%20not%20be%20%E2%80%9Cmade%20the%20subject%20of%20discussion%20between%20a%20majority%20and%20a%20minority.%26quot%3B%20A.%20Thanu%20Pillai%2C%20a%20member%20from%20Travancore%20and%20Cochin%20State%2C%20though%20a%20self-avowed%20%E2%80%98believer%2C'%20argued%20that%20the%20amendment%20could%20amount%20to%20%26quot%3Bcompulsion%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20faith.%26quot%3B%20Sensing%20that%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20the%20Assembly%20was%20turning%20tense%2C%20Rohini%20Kumar%20Chaudhury%2C%20a%20member%20from%20Assam%2C%20remarked%20dryly%3A%20%E2%80%9CMay%20I%20move%20an%20amendment%20to%20that%20of%20Shri%20Kamath%20that%2C%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%98In%20the%20name%20of%20God'%2C%20would%20he%20be%20pleased%20to%20accept%20%E2%80%98In%20the%20name%20of%20Goddess'%3F%E2%80%9D%20Even%20in%20that%20very%20serious%20hour%2C%20Chaudhury's%20intervention%20conjured%20peals%20of%20laughter.%20Later%20on%2C%20Chaudhury%20went%20on%20to%20amplify%E2%80%94especially%20after%20a%20criticism%20of%20the%20proposed%20amendment%20by%20freedom%20fighter%20and%20later%20Rajya%20Sabha%20Member%2C%20Hridya%20Nath%20Kunzru%E2%80%94that%20he%20believed%20in%20a%20Goddess.%20%E2%80%9CI%20belong%20to%20Kamrup%20where%20the%20Goddess%20Kamakhya%20is%20worshipped%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHumour%20Is%20Necessary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20examples%20of%20humour%20and%20wit%20are%20not%20exhaustive%2C%20nor%20are%20they%20politically%20representative.%20But%20the%20intention%20behind%20these%20selections%20is%20merely%20to%20highlight%20how%20key%20protagonists%20often%20found%20themselves%20resorting%20to%20wit%20in%20their%20journey%20towards%20wisdom%20and%20while%20debating%20contentious%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20research%2C%20I%20also%20came%20across%20some%20dubious%20comments%20that%20do%20the%20rounds%20on%20many%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20today%2C%20attributed%20to%20the%20likes%20of%20Sardar%20Vallabhai%20Patel%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20and%20Rajendra%20Prasad.%20Once%2C%20when%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20forgot%20to%20bring%20his%20notes%2C%20Nehru%20is%20said%20to%20have%20remarked%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20seems%20even%20our%20papers%20are%20demanding%20freedom%20from%20us.%E2%80%9D%20On%20another%20occasion%2C%20when%20the%20national%20symbols%20of%20India%20were%20being%20discussed%2C%20Prasad%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20joked%20on%20the%20debate%20over%20choosing%20between%20a%20tiger%20or%20a%20lion%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20long%20as%20it%20is%20not%20goat%2C%20all%20else%20is%20fine.%E2%80%9D%20These%20statements%20should%20still%20be%20considered%20fake%20unless%20someone%20can%20provide%20documented%20evidence%20of%20these%20words%20having%20been%20exchanged%20during%20the%20Assembly%20Debates.%20However%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20veracity%20of%20these%20statements%2C%20there's%20a%20lesson%20we%20must%20draw%20from%20these%20debates%2C%20especially%20in%20today's%20age%20of%20passion%20and%20(mis)information%3A%20%3Cem%3Ethou%20may%20have%20a%20sense%20of%20humour%20because%20the%20Constitution%20hath%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%5BArup%20K.%20Chatterjee%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3