%20film-maker%20and%20founder%20of%20%E2%80%98Calcutta%20Street%20Restaurant%E2%80%99%20in%20London%2C%20shares.%20Hands%20down%20her%20favourite%20of%20these%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekochur%20loti%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20dish%20made%20with%20taro%20plant%20stems).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20delicious%20spicy%20dish%20made%20into%20a%20pate%20and%20cooked%20in%20mustard%20oil%2C%20lots%20of%20ginger%2C%20chillies%20and%20fresh%20chillies.%20Some%20families%20even%20add%20baby%20prawns%20to%20it.%20I%20remember%20mixing%20it%20up%20with%20lots%20of%20rice%20and%20%3Cem%3Eghee%3C%2Fem%3E.%20I%20could%20eat%20an%20entire%20meal%20just%20with%20this.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Arunava%20Banerjee%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731817800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fkolkata-foods-1731682385.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D380569%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Butter%20oozing%20out%20of%20a%20chicken%20cutlet%20to%20zero-waste%20recipes%20made%20from%20plants%2C%20here%20are%20some%20foods%20of%20Kolkata%20that%20have%20won%20chefs'%20hearts%20and%20palates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F380569%2Funique-foods-kolkata-mango-sticky-rice-aloo-r-chops-fallen-kitchen-lakshmi-narayan-shaw%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dr%20Manoj%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20Game-Changing%20Makhana%20Farming%20Methods%20Are%20Making%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20Farmers%20Richer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEuryale%20ferox%2C%20commonly%20known%20as%20fox%20nuts%2C%20lotus%20seeds%20or%20%3Cem%3Emakhana%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20has%20quickly%20become%20a%20prized%20crop%20around%20India.%20Bihar%20alone%20produces%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F236549%2Fbihar-farmer-earns-lakhs-superfood-makhana-entrepreneur-lotus-seeds-fox-nuts-cultivation-farming-india-ana79%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E90%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Emakhana%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20highly%20nutritious%20seed%20sought%20after%20for%20its%20protein%2C%20fibre%2C%20and%20vitamin%20content.%20However%2C%20traditional%20harvesting%20methods%20have%20long%20been%20labour-intensive%2C%20inefficient%2C%20and%20hazardous.%20Fishermen%20and%20farmers%20dive%20into%20deep%2C%20muddy%20ponds%20%E2%80%94%20often%20as%20deep%20as%20eight%20to%2012%20feet%20%E2%80%94%20for%20hours%20to%20collect%20the%20seeds%2C%20risking%20injuries%20and%20infections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecognising%20these%20issues%2C%20Dr%20Manoj%20Kumar%2C%20a%20senior%20scientist%20at%20the%20National%20Research%20Centre%20for%20Makhana%20(NRCM)%2C%20has%20figured%20out%20a%20way%20to%20turn%20%3Cem%3Emakhana%3C%2Fem%3E%20cultivation%20into%20a%20more%20sustainable%20and%20profitable%20agricultural%20practice%2C%20benefiting%20thousands%20of%20farmers%20in%20the%20region.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPerils%20of%20an%20inefficient%20%3Cem%3Emakhana%20%3C%2Fem%3Eharvesting%20process%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20generations%2C%20families%20like%20Phool%20Dev%20Shahni%E2%80%99s%20in%20Darbhanga%2C%20Bihar%2C%20have%20relied%20on%20traditional%20%3Cem%3Emakhana%3C%2Fem%3E%20farming%20methods.%20Shahni%20would%20spend%20seven%20to%20eight%20hours%20every%20day%20underwater%2C%20surfacing%20every%20eight%20to%2010%20minutes.%20Sharp%20thorns%20on%20the%20plants%20caused%20frequent%20cuts%2C%20while%20the%20muddy%20water%20led%20to%20skin%20infections.%20This%20backbreaking%20process%20discouraged%20younger%20generations%20from%20continuing%20the%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn