cancer%20in%20India%3A%20A%20crisis%20that%20demands%20attention%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20around%2075%2C000%20children%20in%20India%20are%20diagnosed%20with%20cancer.%20Unlike%20adult%20cancers%2C%20paediatric%20cancer%20has%20its%20own%20unique%20challenges%20%E2%80%94%20requiring%20specialised%20treatment%20but%20also%2C%20crucially%2C%20if%20caught%20early%2C%20has%20a%20high%20survival%20rate.%20In%20high-income%20countries%2C%20more%20than%2080%20percent%20of%20kids%20with%20cancer%20survive.%20But%20in%20India%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20still%20only%20about%2020%20percent%2C%20mainly%20because%20so%20many%20families%20can%E2%80%99t%20afford%20or%20access%20the%20necessary%20treatment%20in%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20difference%20highlights%20the%20urgent%20necessity%20to%20tackle%20structural%20challenges%20in%20paediatric%20cancer%20treatment%20in%20India.%20Specialised%20care%20is%20often%20available%20only%20in%20major%20cities%2C%20and%20treatment%20is%20a%20long%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamilies%20from%20rural%20or%20underserved%20areas%20need%20to%20travel%20long%20distances%20to%20reach%20hospitals%2C%20spending%20huge%20amounts%20on%20travel%20and%20stay%2C%20and%20often%20facing%20heartbreaking%20choices%20about%20work%2C%20income%2C%20and%20even%20relocating.%20Beyond%20the%20financial%20burden%2C%20the%20emotional%20toll%20on%20families%2C%20who%20may%20have%20to%20abandon%20work%20or%20uproot%20their%20lives%2C%20adds%20an%20overwhelming%20strain.%20This%20highlights%20the%20need%20for%20a%20comprehensive%20approach%20that%20addresses%20not%20only%20treatment%20but%20also%20support%20services%20for%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPrioritising%20early%20detection%20and%20affordable%20access%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20childhood%20cancer%2C%20early%20detection%20is%20key.%20Simple%20scr